.sh NAME
gtbld \*- GRINNELL lookup table load
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd
gtbld
mode [threshold]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it
Gtbld
can be used to load the GRINNELL hardware lookup table with preset
values. Currently the table may be loaded with the values 0->4095
(standard), 4095->0 (complement), or 0+4095 (threshold).  Quite often this
program is used to remap images created from the T.V. camera for manipulation
by programs running on the UNIVAC 1108 (The GRINNELL says black is zero,
the 1108 (XAP) says white is zero).
.s3
The first parameter determines the mode:
.sp 1
	s is standard mode  0 -> 4095,
.sp 0
	r is reverse mode  4095 -> 0,
.sp 0
	t is threshold mode.
.sp 0
The optional second parameter gives a twelve bit integer threshold value.
